.TH SIMPLE_SHELL "Nov 2025" "1.0" "Holberton School"
.SH NAME
simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a program that reproduces the functionality of a Unix/Linux terminal shell.
It is a lightweight, educational implementation of the bash shell.
.PP
Once launched, it displays a prompt ($) with personal pwd where you can type commands.
The program parses your input, splits it into arguments, and executes the corresponding command.
.SH GETTING STARTED
.PP
.B $ ./simple_shell
.PP
The shell will then display a prompt ($) and wait for your commands. Type exit to quit (EOF)
.SH USAGE EXAMPLES
.TP
.B $ ls
Lists files in the current directory
.TP
.B $ pwd
Shows the full path of the current working directory
.TP
.B $ echo "Welcome"
Prints text to the screen
.TP
.B $ cat file.txt
Displays the contents of a text file
.TP
.B $ env
Lists all environment variables in the system
.SH HOW IT WORKS
The shell operates through the following steps:
.TP
.B 1. Display Prompt
A simple "$" invites you to type a command
.TP
.B 2. Read Input
Your text is read from the keyboard
.TP
.B 3. Parse
The line is split into words (the command and its arguments)
.TP
.B 4. Execute
The shell locates the command and executes it with the provided arguments
.TP
.B 5. Return to Prompt
The cycle repeats, waiting for the next command.
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Terminates the program and closes the shell
.TP
.B env
Displays all available environment variables
.SH CODE STRUCTURE
.TP
.B main.c
Entry point of the program
.TP
.B prompt.c
Manages prompt display
.TP
.B read_line.c
Retrieves commands typed by the user
.TP
.B split.c
Splits commands into arguments
.TP
.B execute.c
Executes the parsed commands
.TP
.B environnement.c
Accesses environment variables
.SH COMPILATION
Use a standard C compiler:
.PP
.B $ gcc -o simple_shell *.c
.SH AUTHORS
MOUYSSET Alexandre -- Zinini Nabil

